text.tspan: Development of Web Interface for GH Farm Produce
Hemang Gandhi, Keivan Shah. Mentors: Yogita Mali, Uma Sharma, Parin Chheda.

flowRoot.flowPara: ~ Presently the Producer has to manually enter the data for each produce in the farm. As the size of farm and its produce increases it becomes more and more difficult to maintain the entire Logging system. By making the entire system automated and available online it would make it easier to maintain the records and also adds opportunities for the producer to sell his produce online.

~ On the consumer end the system for buying crops needs to be made more transparent. Presently the consumers that order crops online are unaware about the details of the produce they receive. Making a system that shows the actual photos of the produce that the consumer intends to buy would help making the system more transparent.
1. Make a system to log the data from the weighing
machine to the website.
2. Make a proper system for placing orders for the farm
produce.
3. Create interfaces for different users (Consumer,
Producer, Admin) with different access rights.
4. Make a system to generate analytics for the logged data
that can be accessed by the producer.
5. Make the entire system secure and able to handle
concurrent usage by number of users.
6. Host the website on a server and make it available to
everyone.
7. Create a user and admin manual for the entire system.

~ The main aim of this project to make a automated system for the Logging and Monitoring of Farm produce from greenhouses and make an e-commerce website to sell the produce. The system consists of three users namely producer, consumer and admin.

~ Each producer can have multiple weighing machines and can get analytics about the amount of produce logged, sold and wasted. The producer can get orders for his produce from different customers via the system which he can either deliver or reject according to his discretion. The producer can set a minimum and daily maximum limit of purchase for each particular crop.

~ The consumer can purchase different crops which are currently available from multiple producers in accordance with the daily maximum limit set for each crop by the respective producer. The consumer can also rate the producers.
~ The admin is the caretaker of the entire system. The admin adds producers and weighing machines into the system. The admin has access to the entire database.
~ For more details visit our github repository:
https://github.com/eYSIP-2017/eYSIP-2017_Development_of_Web_Interface_for_GH_Farm_Produce
